document_data.History:
In [[1372 DR]], both [[Bruenor Battlehammer]] and [[Obould Many-Arrows]] signed the treaty. It ended the fierce war between the newly recovered [[Dwarf|dwarven]] kingdom and the beginnings of the [[orc]] realm known as the [[Many-Arrows|Kingdom of Many-Arrows]].
{{quote
|For the good of their respective peoples, they put their names to the Treaty of Garumn's Gorge, recognizing the Kingdom of Many-Arrows and forever changing the face of the [[Silver Marches]].
|excerpt from ''[[The Orc King]]''
}}

As of [[1409 DR]], the two kingdoms were still at peace, although Bruenor had expressed sincere regret on numerous occasions.<ref>
